    {
      "authorString": "Dr. Sample Renderer",
      "time": "2024-03-15T14:05:00-05:00",
      "text": "ANAPHYLAXIS TO PENICILLIN — confirmed by allergist at Breadth Test Medical Center. Patient counseled to avoid ALL penicillin-class antibiotics including amoxicillin, ampicillin, amoxicillin-clavulanate, piperacillin-tazobactam, and to use caution with cephalosporins given possible cross-reactivity (estimated 1-2% with newer generation cephalosporins, higher with first-generation agents sharing similar R1 side chains). Patient was prescribed an epinephrine auto-injector (carries two), educated on use, and given an anaphylaxis action plan. Medical alert bracelet recommended and obtained. This note is deliberately long to exercise the renderer's handling of multi-sentence annotation text that wraps across several lines in the generated PDF output."
    }
